[9.0,"o","\r\n"]
[9.2,"o","\u001b[2mLoading behavior floor...\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[10.7,"o","\u001b[1m=== MEMORY.md (always-on rules) ===\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[11.1,"o","# MEMORY.md — Always-On Non-Negotiable Rules\r\n"]
[11.5,"o","\u001b[33m## ⚠️ QUESTIONS GET ANSWERS, NOT IMPLEMENTATION\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[11.9,"o","A question (\"why...\", \"what is...\", \"do we need...?\") gets an answer and stops.\r\n"]
[12.3,"o","\u001b[33m## ⚠️ DELETION SAFETY\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[12.7,"o","Never hard-delete files. Move anything to be \"deleted\" into a\r\n"]
[13.1,"o","`.trash/<YYYY-MM-DD>_<what>/` folder at your project root, preserving original\r\n"]
[13.5,"o","filenames.\r\n"]
[13.9,"o","\u001b[33m## No Fake Fallbacks\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[14.3,"o","If a task fails (timeout, build error, etc.), report failure and stop. Never\r\n"]
[14.7,"o","substitute mockups, placeholders, or generated content when the task asked for\r\n"]
[15.1,"o","real output. Failure is preferable to fake.\r\n"]
[15.5,"o","[... 9 more rules ...]\r\n"]
[15.9,"o","\u001b[1m=== comms CORE.md (comms invariants) ===\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[16.3,"o","Line 1 is a bold verdict; bold carries the spine; front-load every line.\r\n"]
[16.7,"o","[... full file injected ...]\r\n"]
[17.0,"o","\u001b[1m=== comms DIGEST ===\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[17.875,"o","[comms digest] Line 1 = bold verdict; state uncertainty honestly. Bold carries\r\n"]
[18.75,"o","the spine (bold-only test); bold budget ~25%. No dashes as clause breaks.\r\n"]
[19.625,"o","Front-load every line. Condensed unless depth asked. Exact-format outputs\r\n"]
[20.5,"o","(command confirmations, NO_REPLY) exempt.\r\n"]
[22.75,"o",""]
[25.0,"o","\u001b[H\u001b[2J\u001b[3J"]
[25.0,"o","  \u001b[1mWhat changes, from the first prompt:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[25.9,"o","  · Never hard-deletes: a dated .trash/ folder instead\r\n"]
[26.8,"o","  · Never fakes a passing result: failure is reported as failure\r\n"]
[27.7,"o","  · Answers first, no padding\r\n"]
[28.6,"o","  · Questions get answers, not surprise edits\r\n"]
